Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting significant renal dysfunction, possibly acute or chronic kidney disease with nephrotic-range proteinuria. Low HbA1c excludes chronic hyperglycemia. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Prompt nephrology evaluation is recommended.
